<p>Therefore, in this case, the old mother will receive only 33.33% of the inheritance, while a cousin (or his descendants, whom the deceased person may not have even encountered in his entire life) will receive 66.67%.</p>
<p>One might question the rationale behind this distribution and whether any divine wisdom can be perceived in it.</p>
<p><strong>3rd Example: Sister will get much more share in inheritance than the mother and the wife</strong></p>
<p>Even if the sister is married, she will still receive a larger share of the inheritance compared to the mother or the wife.</p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 30.3167%; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="4">
<tbody>
