<td style="width: 23.4863%; height: 24px; border: 1px solid #000000;">Wife</td>
<td style="width: 34.3531%; height: 24px; background-color: #bfedd2; border: 1px solid #000000;">1/4</td>
<td style="width: 42.4156%; height: 24px; background-color: #fbeeb8; border: 1px solid #000000;">25%</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 24px;">
<td style="width: 23.4863%; height: 24px; border: 1px solid #000000;">Sister</td>
<td style="width: 34.3531%; height: 24px; background-color: #bfedd2; border: 1px solid #000000;">3/4</td>
<td style="width: 42.4156%; height: 24px; background-color: #fbeeb8; border: 1px solid #000000;">75%</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p>Moreover, even if a deceased person has a daughter, still half of the property will go to the sister (even if she is married). </p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 30.6132%; height: 72px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="4">
